-- Danish June forex reserves rise to 438.2 bln DKK
-- By Shida Chayesteh
-- Wed Jul 02, 2014 10:15AM EDT
-- None



COPENHAGEN, July 2 (Reuters) - Denmark's foreign exchange reserves, a monetary policy tool, rose to 438.2 billion Danish crowns ($80.27 billion) in June from 436.7 in May, the central bank said on Wednesday.

